name: **Fox Island**
description: Fox Island V865-692 Sheet 85 A small outlier on the NW of the largest island of all locally, Dunkerron West, fully but barely separated, and unremarkable. Illaunreanageah at V861-697, passed on the way out, is much the more interesting, small, flat, and salt marsh to its tip. Camping should only occur at neaps, as seaweed litters even the highest point.
